qas.question: Axons grouped together are known as what?
An axon that can greatly increase speed of signals is wrapped in what?
Myelin is what color in the brain?
Most of the space in the brain is made up of what structures?
Grey matter of the brain consist of lots of what?

context: Most of the space in the brain is taken up by <a3_0>axons<a3_0/>, which are often bundled together in what are called <a0_0>nerve fiber tracts<a0_0/>. A myelinated axon is wrapped in a fatty insulating <a1_0>sheath of myelin<a1_0/>, which serves to greatly increase the speed of signal propagation. (There are also unmyelinated axons). Myelin is <a2_0>white<a2_0/>, making parts of the brain filled exclusively with nerve fibers appear as light-colored white matter, in contrast to the darker-colored grey matter that marks areas with high densities of <a4_0>neuron cell bodies<a4_0/>.
